               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1300" notAfter="1400">1300-1400</t:date>
                  
                  <t:ab type="history">Gadām. The number of monks might be very small today, but in the past there was a strong monastic community. The manuscripts are stored in the treasury which seems to have been formerly used as rock-hewn church. A built facade nearby belongs to another rock-hewn chruch, the main church of the site. 
                     From the slope, the people point to a place on the plain below which is said to be the birth place of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">King Yoḥannǝs IV</t:persName>
                  </t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/ZEA.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure>20 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea001">ZEA-001</t:ref> “Rite of the Passion Week”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea002">ZEA-002</t:ref> “Four Gospels”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea003">ZEA-003</t:ref> “Missal”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea004">ZEA-004</t:ref> “Praise of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea005">ZEA-005</t:ref> “Story of ʾabunä Sälama”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea006">ZEA-006</t:ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea007">ZEA-007</t:ref> “Synaxarion (the second half of the year)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea008">ZEA-008</t:ref> “Mǝʿraf”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea009">ZEA-009</t:ref> “Psalter”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea010">ZEA-010</t:ref> “Miracles of Jesus”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea011">ZEA-011</t:ref> “Psalter”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea012">ZEA-012</t:ref> “ Catoholic Epistles; Revealation of John”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea013">ZEA-013</t:ref> “Book of the Marriage Ritual; Order of the Monastic Proffession”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea014">ZEA-014</t:ref> “Dǝggwa on Easter; ʾƎzl; Praise of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea015">ZEA-015</t:ref> “Five Pillars of Mystery”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea016">ZEA-016</t:ref> “Book of the Letter”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea017">ZEA-017</t:ref> “Missal”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea018">ZEA-018</t:ref> “Book of the Funeral Rite”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESzea019">ZEA-019</t:ref> “Psalter”; <t:ref type="mss" 